NUMBER 2657
NAME Catacombs, rubble pile
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A large pile of rubble totally covers the west wall, the result of a cave-in
many years ago. The rubbles consists of the shattered pieces of the large
white bricks used in the construction of the long tunnels found here. A few
spiders scramble over the discarded stone, weaving intricate webs between
the jagged gaps in the pile.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2656
ITEM 0 213
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Though the rubble fills the entire western section of this small space
you note that it offers many handholds...if you don't mind sticking your
hands near the numerous spiderwebs that cover the pile.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 103
VARIABLE rubp
VARIABLE MIKERATGEN
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You can't go there.
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 0
  CLEARVERB
    SKILLCHECK 5 -5 rubp
      IFVAR rubp => 80
        ECHO PLAYER You scamper up the side of the rubble pile as if it were nothing but a set of stairs.
        ECHO OTHERS %N scampers up the side of the rubble pile as if it were nothing but a set of stairs.
        MOVE 2658
        AFFECT 2658
        ECHO OTHERS %N clambers into view.
        AFFECT 2656
      ENDIF
        IFVAR rubp =< 79
          IFVAR rubp => 0
            ECHO PLAYER Carefully avoiding the loose rocks in the pile of rubble, not to mention the spiderwebs, you make your way to the top.
            ECHO OTHERS %N slowly and methodically makes %h way to the top of the rubble pile.
            MOVE 2658
            AFFECT 2658
            ECHO OTHERS %N clambers into view.
            AFFECT 2656
	  ENDIF
        ENDIF
          IFVAR rubp < 0
            IFVAR rubp => -35
              ECHO PLAYER You step on a loose stone in the pile and fall backwards, regaining your balance and landing on your feet as you hit the floor.
              ECHO OTHERS %N steps on a loose stone in the pile and falls backwards, luckily %s regains %h balance and manages to land on %h feet.
            ENDIF
          ENDIF
            IFVAR rubp < -35
              ECHO PLAYER You stick your hand into a spiderweb and instantly feel a sharp sting on your hand, which causes you to lose your handholds and pinwheel backwards off the pile!
              ECHO OTHERS About halfway up the pile %N screams in pain and then pinwheels backwards off the pile, landing on the floor with a thud!
              POSITION LAY
       ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The clicking of spider legs on stone sends a small shiver up your spine.
  ECHO OTHERS %N shudders slightly.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2658
NAME Top of rubble
INDOOR_GROUND
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The conglomeration of sharp rocks makes the top of this pile an
uncomfortable place to be. The rocks dig, painfully, into any flesh they
meet, and the larger than normal spiders crawl across any exposed they
can find. The numerous cobwebs make it hard to see anything, but it seems
like there is no further egress along the pile of rubble. It looks like
going down the pile is the only exit.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 2657
VARIABLE spader
IFENTRY
 IFITEM 0
   ECHO PLAYER You note that someone has uncovered a small hole amidst the rubble.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  RANDOM dummy3 1 100 0
  ADD dummy3 PER
    IFVAR dummy3 => 135
      ADD spader 1
        IFVAR spader = 1
          ECHO PLAYER You manage to find a small hole that looks interesting...
          ECHO OTHERS %N points out the small hole %s has just found...
          NEWITEM 0 336 ADJ1=294
        ENDIF
        ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER You don't find anything of note.
     ENDIF
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The hole is very dark, but you think that it extends a fair way down. You
think that you can dimly see some object very far down...perhaps if you
pushed your arm all the way down...
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE tamark
VARIABLE tamark1
IFPREVERB PUSH 0
  CLEARVERB
   RANDOM dummy4 1 100 0
   ADD dummy4 AGI
     IFVAR dummy4 => 145
        IFVAR tamark = 0
          ADD tamark 1
           ECHO PLAYER You reach into the hole and feel around...your hand closes around something and when you try to pull it up you feel it raise partway and then hear a grinding sound emanating from somewhere far away.
           ECHO OTHERS %N reaches into the hole and seems to be trying to pull something up...you can also hear a loud grinding noise emanating from somewhere.
	   AFFECT 2656
           ECHO ALL You hear a loud grinding noise echoing from somewhere nearby, it sounds muffled.
           AFFECT 2658
        ENDIF
        ELSE
          ECHO PLAYER You reach into the hole and immediately feel your hand close around something moving and furry...whatever it is bites you!
          ECHO OTHERS %N yells in pain and surprise a moment after sticking %h hand down into the hole.
          DAMAGE SLASH 5 %N yelps in pain!
     ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2659
NAME Catacombs, strange contraption
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A curtain of sticky cobwebs hangs from the ceiling of the half-dome shaped
tunnel. The metal rails, laying in the center of the floor, are thickly
coated with rust and the logs that they are fastened to have swelled and
split in many spots. Laying, on its side, against the western wall is a long
rectangular contraption. The profusion of webs covering it makes it hard to
discern any details from a quick glance. The tunnel itself continues,
in a curve, to the northwest and southwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 2661
EXIT SW 2654
ITEM 0 349 ADJ1=178
EXTEND 0 covered with cobwebs
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=2660
