NUMBER 2660
NAME Inside strange contraption
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
Cobwebs swing lazily in the breeze caused by your movement, covering an
odd assortment of items. Shattered glass, from the numerous broken windows
cover the floor, crunches under the trodding of feet. Bolted into the floor
are numerous benches with red plastic cushions that have been ripped in
many spots. A dirty wool-like substance leaks from the holes in the cushions
filling the area with a foul stench. Next to each bench, extending from
floor to ceiling, is a circular metal pole. All of the poles have long
since rusted. A cobweb covered opening leads back outside.
