NUMBER 2662
NAME Laboratory
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A fine layer of dust covers the contents of this workroom. Its contents
lie undisturbed, untouched by any hands for many centuries. Piles of
rotting leather and papers are scattered along the length of the shelves
attached to the northern wall of the room. A dusty glass orb sits
prominently on a stout oak table against the eastern wall. Scattered around
the orb are the broken glass remnants of various test tubes and beakers.
Painted on the floor of the room, in a circle, are various symbols of
beasts. A cauldron and an open cage sit, undisturbed, in the center of
the circle.
*DESCRIPTION_END
