NUMBER 578
NAME Kvantar Underground
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
INDOOR_GROUND
MONSTER_GROUP 16
*DESCRIPTION_START
A wooden sacrificial altar stands in the middle of this circular chamber.
The altar is engraved with images of a red, glowing stone, and has a bowl
shaped depression at one end, possibly to catch the blood of victims. Unlike
the other rooms down here, the earthen walls are partially covered by wood
boards with paintings upon them. At the northern end of the chamber the
circular walls come together to form a side. Sticking out of the walls
are two skulls, one to the left and one to the right of the side. A
passage leads out of this chamber to the east.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 575
ITEM 0 432
ITEM 1 352 ADJ1=401
ITEM 2 352 ADJ2=402
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The crudely rendered paintings seem to represent the religious beliefs of
the Kvantar. In the first panel, a normal humanoid is shown standing before
a red, glowing stone, bathing in its light. The second panel shows the same
humanoid, now a Kvantar, engaged in various activities including killing and
eating other humanoids. The third panel shows the same Kvantar in a more
advanced stage of sickness. It seems that the Kvantar consider this more
advanced stage as a sign of great power. The fourth panel depicts the
Kvantar being absorbed into the red glowing stone. The fifth and last
panel depicts the stone growing and metamorphasizing into a giant Kvantar
that goes on to slay humanoids.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The left skull has been carved from wood and has a circular hole at its top.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The right skull has been carved from wood and has a circular hole at its top.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB TURN 1
	CLEARVERB
	EQUAL WHICHWAY 0
	IFVAR LEFT = 0
		EQUAL LEFT 1
		ECHO ALL The left skull is now in a clockwise position.
		EQUAL WHICHWAY 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR LEFT ! 0
		IFVAR WHICHWAY = 0
			EQUAL LEFT 0
			ECHO ALL The left skull is now in a counter clockwise position.
			IFITEM 3
				REMOVEITEM 3
				ECHO ALL The opening slams shut.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN 2
	CLEARVERB
	EQUAL OTHERWAY 0
	IFVAR RIGHT = 0
		IFVAR LEFT ! 1
			ECHO ALL The right skull is now in a counter clockwise position.
			EQUAL RIGHT 1
			EQUAL OTHERWAY 1
		ENDIF
		IFVAR LEFT = 1
			ECHO ALL The right skull is now in a counter clockwise position. You here a click as the skull locks into place. Beams of red light shoot out of both the left and right skulls. As the light strikes the wall, the rock seems to melt into blood, revealing an opening to another chamber!
			EQUAL RIGHT 1
			NEWITEM 3 72 VAL2=1000
			EQUAL OTHERWAY 1
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	IFVAR RIGHT ! 0
		IFVAR OTHERWAY = 0
			ECHO ALL The right skull is now in a clockwise position.
			EQUAL RIGHT 0
			IFITEM 3
				REMOVEITEM 3
				ECHO ALL The opening slams shut.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
