NUMBER 965
NAME Caverns, crystal fountain
*DESCRIPTION_START
Smooth columns of natural quartz and other crystalline materials form walls of delicate pastel shades. These colors are repeated in crystal blocks, set together to create a basin for the fountain shooting up through the floor. The drops sound pure tones as they strike the water, like those of crystal goblets clinking together in a toast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CAVE
MINEC
DARKNESS
EXIT O 964
;
ITEM 0 197 ADJ1=77
;crystal fountain
PUT 0 198 VAL2=100
;water (casts spell for temporary AG bonus when drunk)
ITEM 3 44 ADJ1=491
;flat stone
PUT 3 79 VAL2=967
IFPREVERB DRINK -1
	IFVAR RAC < 7
		IFVAR ARCHNUM = 198
			EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
			ECHO PLAYER You scoop up some water from the fountain and take a sip.
			ECHO OTHERS %N scoops up some water from the fountain and take a sip.%c [Round: 5 sec]
			SPELL 515
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
As you look closely at the fitted crystal blocks they seem unnaturally perfect.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
The surface is mirror smooth; the falling drops leave no ripples, they just gently to melt into the water. Crystal blocks color the water near them, giving the pool the look of a swirling pastel rainbow.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFVERB TOUCH 0
	ECHO PLAYER Strange, you feel nothing at all as you reach down into the water and your fingers leave no wake nor ripple.
ENDIF
;
