NUMBER 901
NAME Mirdaal, Fish Pond
*DESCRIPTION_START
A marble-lined oval pool twenty paces long and half as wide begins at the end of the path from the southeast. Thick, sticky scum prevents you from seeing below the surface. The weeds, prevalent elsewhere in the garden, are sparse here and nothing grows within five feet of the pool's edge.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SE 903
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
ITEM 0 324 ADJ1=444
; oval pool
ITEM 1 337
; weeds
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Once-white blocks of marble, now stained and lichen covered, were fitted together carefully when the pool was constructed. Though cosmetically degraded by years of neglact, the construction is still very sound.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
The mucky water moves slightly as you watch but whether caused by a
slight breeze or some aquatic agent, you cannot tell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The few weeds are particularly sickly looking; their leaves are yellowed and the edges curled under.
*DESCRIPTION_END
