NAME Mirdaal, Great Hall
*DESCRIPTION_START
Three large chandeliers hang from the ceiling. Probably oil or gas powered, they look as though they would have brightly lighted this reception area. Some life-sized paintings once adorned the walls along with a number of sculptures but these have all been damaged beyond restoration. The thick woolen carpet must have been luxurious but now is rotting and smells of mold and other things less pleasant. A faded pattern is still discernable in the fabric, but only just.
*DESCRIPTION_END
