This great room provided workspace for the chefs and assistant cooks who daily prepared food for the inhabitants of Mirdaal. Large ovens line the northern wall, while a large pantry dominates the southern. In the center of the room are large tables and long counters. Shattered crockery is everywhere but the food is all long gone. A stairway to the west leads down and to the east is the Banquet Hall.
