NUMBER 46
NAME Keyboard, Underside
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a vast rectangular room with circuitry lining the walls and large,
gray, plastic squares in the ceiling. There is a thin, nearly invisible
string stemming from each square to a different part of Tannelorn. As
Tannelorn moves, so do the plastic panels in the ceiling yet there seems to
be no method to their chaotic motion. You hear a loud clacking sound from
above and somewhere off in the distance you can make out the grinding tones
of fast and furious music. The floor is made of glass and looking through
it, you can see the world of Andor in its entirety. People milling about in
various directions, going about their daily business. Watching them from
this vantage you are reminded of an ant farm and you wonder briefly if you
could hit one of them with a spitball.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 206

IFENTRY
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
  GMMSG ** %n just logged into Tannelorn's office.
  ECHO PLAYER A mysterious force moves you to the city.
  ECHO OTHERS A mysterious force moves %n to the city.
  MOVE 201
  ENDIF
ENDIF
